{
  "stem": "4753.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And very, very suddenly hap-- happened everything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "First, the occupation announced in 19-- March 19.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then about 25th, I think, March 25th, the yellow star and the yellow armband came to effect-- armband for the soldiers and stars for the civil-- civilians.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everything was going too fast.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The SS men came to the people's door, knocked, preferable at night when you were asleep, and asking for the head of the family, beating him senseless to confess where are the fortune of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And between the time, you had to donate your typewriter, radio, and bicycle-- because that's what we had, what was a lifeline for us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father, every night about midnight or so, was listening to the radio, to the BBC before the occupation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That's the British Broadcasting Company.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that gave us some hope.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because somehow, we knew what was happening outside of Hitler's territory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But after the, the radio was taken away, we had no way to know what's going on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Curfew came in.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were allowed to go out between 12:00 or-- and 2:00, or something like that, to take care of errands.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What you couldn't do because when I was standing out in line for, for milk or bread, for example, when I came to the door with my yellow star, they said everything is gone.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the person who stood behind me got all the food, what she was asking for.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So right away, that was horrible things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When they told us we ca-- we have to go the ghetto, appointing the Jews' homes as ghetto, they said we can take everything what we wanted to take, what we can carry in our two hands.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you cannot carry too man-- too many things.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
